<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-11-29T13:12:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-11-29T13:12:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <head>353. Telegram 216018 From the <gloss type="from">Department of
                                State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mission to the United
                                Nations</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d353fn1">Source:
                                National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central
                                Files 1970–1973, DEF 18–6. Confidential; Immediate. Drafted by Black
                                    (<gloss target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>/UNP); cleared in UNP, NEA/RA,
                                    <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>/UNA, <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_SOV1">SOV</gloss>, NEA, UNP,
                                    <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>/DCA, and <gloss target="#t_ACDAIR1">ACDA/IR</gloss>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_DPS2">De Palma</persName> of <gloss target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>.</note>
                            <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d353fn2">The telegram instructed the
                                U.S. delegation to abstain from voting on a revised non-use of force
                                resolution.</note>
                        </head>
                        <dateline><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1972-11-29T18:12:00+00:00">November 29, 1972,
                            1812Z</date>.</dateline>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>Subj:</head>
                            <item>Non-use of Force (<gloss target="#t_NUF1">NUF</gloss>) Res</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="references">
                            <head>Refs:</head>
                            <item>(A) <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 4880; (B) State 207841;
                                (C) State 215438</item>
                        </list>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>USDel instructed to abstain in plenary vote on revised non-aligned
                                    <gloss target="#t_NUF1">NUF</gloss> res (reftel A).</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>USDel should ask for separate vote on sixth preambular para and
                                vote against.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>In explanation of vote on res you should include statement that
                                    <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> considers that nothing in
                                sixth or seventh preambular paras can change Charter provisions
                                regarding legitimate use of force.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>USDel should also add statement to effect that preambular para 8
                                recalls res which <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> opposed. Our
                                opposition to that res remains unchanged notwithstanding our
                                abstention on <gloss target="#t_NUF1">NUF</gloss> res as
                                whole.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>